Paramedics say when they arrived on the scene, they found the toddler and her mother sitting on the pavement outside. JOHANNESBURG - A two-year-old child has drowned at a house in Olivedale in Johannesburg. Paramedics say when they arrived on the scene earlier on Wednesday, they found the toddler and her mother sitting on the pavement outside. After 30 minutes of advanced life support, the little girl was declared dead.ER24's spokesperson Russel Meiring said: It is believed the family pulled the child from the pool and carried her to the sidewalk, an investigation will be launched into this matter. 